# Client build-time config. Vite inlines VITE_* at BUILD time, so these must be
# set wherever the build runs:
#   • Local:  copy this file to apps/client/.env and fill in the values.
#   • Prod:   set the same names as Railway service variables — the Dockerfile
#             declares matching ARGs so they bake into the static bundle.
#
# Both values are safe to expose in client-side code:
#   • a Web3Forms access key is a public submission key
#   • a Discord webhook URL is a write-only post target
#
# HireMe sends every submission to ALL configured channels. With neither set,
# the form falls back to opening a prefilled mail draft (handy for local dev).

# Web3Forms access key — emails each Hire-Me submission to you.
# Free, tied to your email: https://web3forms.com  (Create Access Key)
VITE_WEB3FORMS_KEY=

# Discord channel webhook URL — posts each submission as an alert embed.
# Discord: Server Settings → Integrations → Webhooks → New Webhook → Copy URL
VITE_DISCORD_WEBHOOK_URL=
